Privacy
-------

FastVPN protects and respects our customers' privacy, We ensure our customers remain anonymous when using the service and collect as little information as possible.

Please see our detailed [FastVPN Privacy Policy](https://www.namecheap.com/legal/apps/vpn-privacy-policy) for details on information collected and how it’s used.

To that end: we **DO NOT LOG** any user activity (i.e., sites visited, DNS lookups, emails, etc.)

Here is the information we collect and why we collect it:

Personal Information:

VPN Specific User ID. We create a VPN specific user ID that is shared with the upstream provider for the purpose of:

1. provisioning the product;
2. auditing sales/usage;
3. troubleshooting.

The user ID is what allows us to identify the specific customer for troubleshooting issues and to gather/add to product feedback/features analysis.

Non-PI: Anonymized and/or non-PI data is collected for 2 purposes:

1. Basic analytics such as analysis of the product, product improvement etc. This information is linked to the user ID but the information is not shared. We use a third party processor to generate this info for us.
2. Analysis of crash data, service issues etc. We use a third party processor tool to capture this information when it happens. If a customer has a service issue, we use the user ID to pull the crash data and to work with our upstream provider to resolve the issue.
